Package edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.primitiveDefs Description

The primitiveDefs package is a set of classes which describe and represent the primitive definitions found at the end of XDLRC report files. Serialized data structures representing the set of primitive definitions for a particular family of devices are created during installation to populate these classes. See Technical Report and Documentation for more information.
